communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Vinh Tang Emails - CSWG
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

The full and complete email threads, including replies received by the sender, for emails with the following subjects sent from the email address Vinh.Tang2@seattle.gov between 9/15/23 and 11/8/23 inclusive:
"Piotr Migula", "Yolanda A. Barton", "Laurence Chen", "Greg Wong", "Scott Medrano", "Molly Lathrop", "Kerry J. Keefe", "Loida Erhard", "Lance Fuhrman", "Jayme Stocker", "DeShaun Cole", "Vincent Valentino", "Hannah Pascual", "Jerry Bancroft", "Magin Maier", "Lindsey Rakes", "Angie Bronson", "Jennifer Tam", "Jason Eastman", "Kiana Kelly", "James Frieling", "Amy Nguyen", "Caetê Nicholson", "Benjamin Won", "Erik Strom", "Oksana Bilobran", Trevor Weidl", "Jane Li", "Rebecca S. Widen", "Lisa Gaccione", "Wendy Novotne", "Connect re CSWG Next Steps & Material Change", "Follow Up: CSWG", "Community Surveillance Working Group", "Technology-Assisted Crime Prevention Pilot", "discovery issue", "Sync: Community Surveillance Working Group", "Project Steering Committee: Technology-Assisted Crime Prevention Pilot", "Connect re CSWG Next Steps & Material Change", "ACP - CCTV Strat. Session", "Crime Prevention Tech Strategy", "Crime Prevention Tech Budget Questions", "CCTV and CAO/PAO Next Steps", "FW: Axon / City of Seattle Mayor's Office", "Crime Prevention Technology Briefing", "Public Safety organization", "Discuss Mayor’s technology-assisted crime prevention proposal", "Crime Prevention Technology Pilot Evaluation", "Susan Hintze", "Technology Discussion", "Consult Results:  Request #REQ21084 for Seattle Police Department", "Public Safety Standard Communication Plan"

Please include attachments and any associated metadata. I would prefer the records be provided in their native electronic format if possible.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rose Terse
